      • createTuple

        public Tuple createTuple(EntityKey key,
                         OperationContext operationContext)
        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
        Creates a new tuple for the given entity key.

        Only invoked if no tuple is present yet for the given key. Implementations should not perform a round-trip to the datastore but rather return a transient instance. The OGM engine will invoke GridDialect.insertOrUpdateTuple(EntityKey, TuplePointer, TupleContext) subsequently.

        Columns in the tuple may represent properties of the corresponding entity as well as *-to-one associations to other entities. Implementations may choose to persist the latter e.g. in form of fields or as actual links/relationships to the element representing the associated entity. In case of multi-column keys, the corresponding association role for a given column can be obtained from the passed tuple context.

        Specified by:
        createTuple in interface GridDialect
        Parameters:
        key - The tuple identifier
        operationContext - Contains additional information that might be used to create the tuple
        Returns:
        the created tuple

      • createAssociation

        public Association createAssociation(AssociationKey associationKey,
                                     AssociationContext associationContext)
        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
        Creates a new (empty) association for storing the tuples representing the rows corresponding to the given key.

        Only invoked if the association does not yet exist in the datastore. Implementations should not perform a round-trip to the datastore but rather return a transient instance. The OGM engine will invoke GridDialect.insertOrUpdateAssociation(AssociationKey, Association, AssociationContext) subsequently.

        Specified by:

        associationContext - Contains additional information that might be used to create the association

                                         AssociationTypeContext associationTypeContext)
        Description copied from interface: GridDialect
        Whether the specified association is stored within an entity structure or not. E.g. dialects for document stores may support storing associations within entity documents and would have to return true if this is the case for a given association.

        associationTypeContext - provides additional contextual information about the represented association type, such as the options effectively applying for it
        Returns:

      • executeBackendUpdateQuery

        public int executeBackendUpdateQuery(BackendQuery<String> query,
                                     QueryParameters queryParameters,
                                     TupleContext tupleContext)
        Description copied from interface: QueryableGridDialect
        Returns the result of a native update query executed on the backend.

        Precise semantics of an update are subject to design choices made for the actual database system in the backend. In particular, it may implement non-classical notions of consistency such as eventual consistency (rather than (conflict) serializablity as in most relational SQL database systems).

        Specified by:
        executeBackendUpdateQuery in interface QueryableGridDialect<String>
        Parameters:
        query - the query to execute in a representation understood by the underlying datastore. May have been created by converting a JP-QL query or from a (named) native query.
        queryParameters - parameters passed for this query
        tupleContext - the tuple context
        Returns:
        the number of elements that have been updated.
